The paper discusses the collection and use of runtime provenance information in scientific workflow systems, which is a topic related to data management and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of annotations to specify dependency relationships between inputs and outputs of computation steps, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also describes a reasoning framework for ensuring consistency of the set of dependency annotations, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
